GIRDLER CORPORATION and CherryBurrell Corporation, Plaintiffs-Appellants, v. ABBOTTS DAIRIES, Inc., Defendant-Appellee. No. 6936. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Nov. 22, 1939. Clair W. Fairbank, Oscar W. Jeffery, and S. A. Demma, all of New York City, for plaintiffs-appellants. Geo. W. Hansen and M. Hudson Rathburn, both of Chicago, Ill., (Ames, Thiess, Olson & Mecklenburger, of Chicago, Ill., and Busser & Harding, of Philadelphia, Pa., of counsel), for defendant-appellee.

Before CLARK, BIDDLE, and JONES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

We have considered the record carefully, and finding no error, the decree is affirmed on the opinion of Judge Kirkpatrick, reported in 24 F.Supp. 551.
